roval by legislators the start date is the date of the law or legislative approval in the case of private projects information is taken from public sources such as stock exchange filings annual reports company presentations third party research and press releases in judging the timing of investment decisions for private projects great care was taken to differentiate between large projects receiving environmental approval and proceeding directly to construction and smaller projects where the investment decision hinges on securing financing best care is taken to ensure that recorded data is correct at the time of entry and that each entry is backed with a relevant source the greatest care possible was taken to ensure consistency of information in order make a likeforlike comparison in project costs insofar as the figures rely on disclosure by the organization or company responsible the figures can be considered to be conservative in nature no attempt was made to adjust figures for inflation during the course of research or for consideration of the time value of money validation in the case of stateowned projects validation is carried out where possible with either a member of the consortium epc contractor a relevant state agency or advisors to either party currency projects costs are measured in us dollars where project costs are measured in a local currency amounts are converted to us dollars at the date of the relevant announcement signature or report severity of deviation from original estimates the severity of deviation from original estimates is defined according to set criteria timing status condition ahead of time  of original estimate or below measured in months on time  to  of original estimate minor changes  to  of original estimate medium changes  to  of original estimate major changes over  of original estimate budget status condition ahead of budget  of original budget estimate or below to budget  to  of original budget estimate minor changes  to  of original budget estimate medium changes  to  of original budget estimate major changes over  of original budget estimate changes in scope changes in scope beyond the start date are not accounted for language definitions where guidance is nonspecific as to dates for completion the following is used project to be completed by   december   project to be completed in   december   btg pactual português español english regional sites news press releases contact crimes and frauds sac contact us ombudsman careers culture and values history of btg pactual operating areas recruitment and selection trainee program undergrad summer internship program mba summer internship program internal selection processes partnerships with universities internships and summer jobs technology internship program about us at a glance our core values financial highlights history our partnership senior management statutory officers our competitive advantages our strategy governance social responsibility culture education citizenship our offices research investor relations investment bank investment banking ma and advisory capital markets equity capital markets debt capital markets corporate lending sales  trading market making brokerage research energy trading asset management brazilian asset management latin american asset management merchant banking private equity infrastructure real estate natural resources timberland brazil specialist funds global hedge funds fund administration wealth management banking and transaction products portfolio investment solutions wealth and succession planning corporate advisory specialists family office home  our partnership  senior management statutory officers banco btg pactual sa assis oswaldo oswaldo de assis filho is statuatory director of btg pactual mr assis is based in são paulo mr assis joined pactual in  as a partner he was vicechairman of ubs pactual prior to pactual he was director of banco mercantil de são paulo partner of both planibanc and convenção co