othard michael french trader is fined record €m financial times retrieved  july  france’s market regulator has handed out the largest fine in its history to a trader who made €m from insider trading as the watchdog joins those in the us uk and japan taking a tougher line on financial crimes high quality global journalism requires investment joseph raad “an experienced financier and regular investor” was passed information about the imminent takeover of logistics company geodis by sncf the french state railway in  by his cousin charles rosier a ubs banker at the time close to the deal according to the autorité des marchés financiers   freehills herbert smith  october  french amf imposes record insider dealing fine  lexology lexology retrieved  july  last thursday the french amf imposed a record €m fine on trader joseph raad for engaging in market abuse alleging that he used nonpublic information sourced from a cousin to make €m in  by trading in the shares and options of logistics company geodis the amf claims that charles rosier a banker tipped raad off about an impending transaction that involved french state railway sncf bidding for geodis and that raad bought geodis shares and options worth €m in the fortnight leading up to the announcement of the bid   sanction autorité des marchés financiers  october  retrieved  july    brasileiro adriana  october  brazil billionaire runs  trillion in ubs assets bloomberg lp retrieved  july  esteves is now in charge of about  trillion in ubs assets about  percent more than brazils current gross domestic product of  trillion   schäfer daniel  april  btg chief fined for insider trading financial times retrieved  july  the bank had mentioned “ongoing civil noncriminal investigation in europe” against mr esteves in its ipo prospectus published at the beginning of the month without providing any detail at the time   hl paper iiihc iii minutes of evidence house of commons  parliamentary commission on banking standards retrieved  july